most of those studies indicated that accidents do increase with age. 
And age 60 seems to be the break-point. 

Senator STEVENS. Then why don’t you apply it to Part 135 planes 

that carry people commercially? 

Dr.  JORDAN.  We  do  apply  it  to  Part,  well,  Part  135  operations 
being  operated  under  Part  121  rules,  which  include  aircraft  of  ten 
or  more  seats,  all  of  those  operations  fly  under  Part  121  rules  and 
are  subjected  to  the  Age  60  Rule.  But  the  smaller  operations,  the 
age  limits  do  not  apply.  And  I  think  it’s  a  matter  of  where  you 
draw the line. 

Senator STEVENS. More than nine seats, you mean? 
Dr. JORDAN. Yes. 
Senator  STEVENS.  Well,  no  offense,  but  this  is  a  conundrum—10 
