Senator  BURNS.  For  the  record—the  16  Hour  Rule,  explain  that 

to me, would you, please? 

Mr.  WOERTH.  Yes,  sir,  Mr.  Chairman,  for  quite  some  time  there 
was  a  controversy  over,  if  it,  was  16  hours  really  a  limit,  or  was 
that just a scheduling goal, and we finally had to get a ruling, and 
work  with  the  APA,  in  particular,  on  this,  it  was  known  as  the 
‘‘Whitlow Letter,’’ a person out of the FAA finally determined at 16 

VerDate Nov 24 2008  12:28 Jan 14, 2011 Jkt 063516 PO 00000 Frm 00041 Fmt 6633 Sfmt 6601 S:\GPO\DOCS\63516.TXT SCOM1 PsN: JACKIE

