hours you are done, a pilot cannot get back in a cockpit and fly just 
because  the  airline  was  running  late,  or  somebody  wants  to  con-
tinue the march, the 16 hours is the real limit. The fact that that’s 
twice the normal day—that might have been a midnight shift going 
until the middle of the afternoon the next day, thank God we have 
the  Whitlow  Letter,  but  there  was  still  opposition  within  certain 
airlines  who  didn’t  want  to  live  with  that,  they  wanted  even  more 
hours to be flown, or a duty day to be even longer than that. 

